# Sprint 3.1 – Final Walkthrough: Security & Authentication Layer

This walkthrough documents the complete implementation and verification of the Security Layer (Phase 2), Authentication Business Logic (Phase 3), and Authentication API (Phase 4) for the AlgoPath application.

---

## Changes Implemented

### 1. Dependencies
* **[requirements.txt](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/requirements.txt)**: Added `bcrypt>=4.0.0` for password hashing.
* **[requirements-dev.txt](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/requirements-dev.txt)**: Configured `pytest>=8.0.0` and `httpx>=0.27.0` for backend integration testing.

### 2. Router-Level Dependencies
* **[dependencies.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/dependencies.py)**: Centralized FastAPI dependencies (`get_current_user`, `get_admin_user`, `oauth2_scheme`) to keep the core service layer completely framework-independent.
* **[curriculum.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/routes/curriculum.py)**: Refactored route dependencies to import from `app.dependencies` rather than `app.services.auth_service`.

### 3. Core Security & Authentication Services
* **[password_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/password_service.py)**: Stateless helper class utilizing `bcrypt` for secure hashing and password checking.
* **[jwt_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/jwt_service.py)**: Encapsulates JWT operations and error handling. Exposes `TokenExpiredError` and `TokenInvalidError`.
* **[auth_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/auth_service.py)**: 
  * Rebuilt as the core orchestration service for authentication business logic.
  * Encapsulates domain-specific security errors (`AuthenticationError`, `UserAlreadyExistsError`, `InvalidCredentialsError`, `UserNotFoundError`).
  * Normalizes emails using a private `_normalize_email(email)` method.
  * `register_user(db, register_data) -> UserResponse` creates users, triggers transaction rollback on failures, and returns sanitized DTOs.
  * `login_user(db, login_data) -> TokenResponse` authenticates credentials and returns DTO tokens. Returns generic errors to prevent user email enumeration.
  * `get_user_by_email(db, email) -> User` & `get_user_by_id(db, user_id) -> User` perform query operations returning ORM `User` models for internal orchestration.

### 4. API Endpoints
* **[auth.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/routes/auth.py)**:
  * Exposes thin route controllers: `POST /api/auth/register`, `POST /api/auth/login`, and `GET /api/auth/me`.
  * Standardized response schemas (`response_model`), success status codes, and Swagger descriptions.
  * Ensures `/me` translates ORM models directly to the `UserResponse` DTO.
  * Maps service exceptions to clean REST status codes (`409 Conflict`, `401 Unauthorized`, `500 Internal Server Error`).

